Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager of Public Services Bradford , ON Description The Bradford West Gwillimbury Public Library is a community-focused, single branch Library serving a diverse population of 42,800. The community includes urban and rural areas with most of the population centered in Bradford, which is on the edge of the GTA and adjacent to the Holland Marsh. Easily accessible from Highways 400, 27 and 11, Bradford is a growing community, reflected in the increasing demand for library services. The Library has an opening for a full-time Manager of Public Services. Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer, this position is a member of the management team, with whom they work to determine public service priorities and support the Library's strategic initiatives. This position is responsible for scheduling, planning, organizing, supervising, training, and coordinating workflow activities in the three areas of the department: customer service, information service and the creative lab. Specific responsibilities include but are not limited to: Responsible for providing strategic leadership in innovative service development to ensure the library meets and exceeds established public service objectives; Manages department staff, which involves hiring, training, conducting performance appraisals, coaching/mentoring, and professional development; Directly supervises the Senior Customer Services Specialist, the Customer Services Specialists, the Information Specialists and the Emerging Technologies Specialist; Provides input into the creation, implementation and management of policies and procedures and ensures that they are understood and followed by the public and employees; Monitors and approves work schedules for staff, while ensuring operational levels are maintained; Investigates and resolves escalated customer complaints and concerns; Maintains a calm professional manner in difficult situations and applies effective communication and de-escalation techniques; Troubleshoots problems with audio-visual equipment in meeting and program rooms; Aids and instructs library users with questions concerning technology and devices and assists photocopier users with software and printing issues; Performs all service desk functions related to the circulation of materials, customer registration, reservations, and service charge assessments; Prepares and reconciles weekly/monthly revenues received at the service desk, ensuring amounts balance with records; Oversees the accurate and timely processing of collection agency accounts; In collaboration with the Deputy CEO, works with vendors to develop, maintain and troubleshoot the Library's Integrated Automation Systems and other automated circulation related systems; Provides direction and support to the Emerging Technologies Specialist to ensure high­ caliber education and program opportunities are available at the Creative Lab; Pursues new technologies and innovations, and identifies opportunities for further consideration; Leads and participate in committees and cross functional teams as required; Participates in planning capital projects and assists with special projects as assigned by the Chief Executive Officer; Compiles and prepares reports and month end statistics for the CEO and Library Board; Maintains confidentiality under the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act and other related and applicable legislation and ensures staff follow best practices; Supports the mission, vision and values of Bradford West Gwillimbury Public Library; Complies with the Occupational Health and Safety Act and Regulations, and the Corporate Health &amp; Safety Policy and related procedures; This position is currently vacant. This position offers a salary range of $72,912 to $91,140 per year based on 35 hours per week, including some evenings and weekends, plus a competitive benefit package including OMERS pension plan. Qualifications: Training and knowledge in the above, with completion of a post-graduate degree in Library and Information Sciences or an equivalent combination of education and experience; Minimum of 5 years public library and supervisory experience preferably in public service; Demonstrated supervisory, performance management, leadership and team building skills; Knowledgeable about emerging trends, new technologies, information services and customer-centric models of service delivery; Strong organizational skills with the ability to balance priorities and meet deadlines; Ability to cope with high levels of interruptions, exercise discretion and exceptional judgement; Ability to maintain cooperative and courteous relationships with other staff, library users, and staff of various organizations and businesses; Ability to work days, evenings and weekends; Fluent in English (reading, writing, verbal), other language fluency considered an asset; Satisfactory Police Record Check; Thorough working knowledge of relevant statutes and regulations including OPLA, FIPPPA, OHSA, and the Copyright Act; Interested candidates are invited to forward their resume and cover letter by midnight on Sunday July 14, 2024 to: Nina Cunniff, Acting CEO Bradford West Gwillimbury Public Library 425 Holland St. West careers@bradford.library.on.ca We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those being considered for an interview will be contacted. In accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of personal information is collected under the authority of the Municipal Act, and only be used for candidate selection. The Bradford West Gwillimbury Public Library is committed to equity in employment. As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to establishing a qualified workforce that is reflective of the diverse population we serve. All candidates must be able to promote a culture of inclusiveness and work with a diverse population of employees and the public. We encourage applications from Indigenous peoples, racialized people, persons with disabilities, and those who identify as 2SLGBTQ+. The Bradford West Gwillimbury Public Library is committed to providing accommodation based on any human rights protected ground throughout the recruitment and selection process. If you require accommodation, please notify us when contacted for an interview and we will work with you to meet your needs. Compensation Starting at $72,912 Closes: 14 July, 2024 Bradford-West Gwillimbury Public Library (ON)-CAN Bradford , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
