Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Senior Circulation Assistant (Regular Full-Time) 2 Positions - Parkgate &amp; Capilano Libraries (JP#24-09L) North Vancouver , BC Description At North Vancouver District Public Library, we inspire learning, discovery, creativity and collaboration in our community. Serving almost 90,000 residents at three full-service locations and one Express Library throughout the beautiful District of North Vancouver, we are proud to provide free and equitable access to welcoming spaces, diverse collections and digital resources, a wide range of technology and computers, including StoryLab, and so much more. Proudly late fine free, our libraries are the destination for our growing community to connect, share, and inspire. NVDPL is looking for two regular full-time Senior Circulation Assistants to ensure the smooth operation of the Circulation team in the absence of the Circulation Supervisor, supervise the Library Pages and their work, and provide front line service to the general public. What we can offer you At NVDPL, we believe in building community and relationships, nurturing innovation while honouring tradition, embracing exploration, creativity, and fun, and supporting human potential and enabling excellence. Reporting to the Circulation Supervisor, you will supervise the library’s Page staff and perform a variety of tasks as part of the Circulation team, including but not limited to, checking library materials in and out, registering patrons, collecting fees, resolving patron complaints, reconciling monies received and preparing bank deposits. What you’ll be doing In addition to the primary tasks noted above, aspects of the role will also include: Providing services to patrons and visitors in person, online and over the phone Training Pages, supporting the training of new library assistants, and assisting with team scheduling issues Maintaining the periodical and newspaper collection Processing hold requests and new, damaged, lost and overdue materials Performing opening and closing procedures Setting up book trucks for shelving and shelving library items Packing and unpacking delivery boxes Ordering supplies needed for daily circulation tasks Addressing problems with multi-function devices, washrooms, and behavioural issues that arise in the public space Other related tasks What you’ll need to succeed Considerable experience completing circulation tasks in a public library team environment A commitment to service excellence, recognizing that the library serves members of the public from all walks of life An understanding of circulation-related policies, procedures, automation, standard software applications (eg. Micosoft) and public library operations A demonstrated ability to provide leadership and supervision in close partnership with the Circulation Supervisor, requiring strong communication skills Organizational skills and attention to detail Leading by example while demonstrating your ability to deal courteously, effectively and efficiently with the public and maintain working relationships with other employees Physical capacity to handle heavy library materials and to stand for long periods Ability to take initiative, ask for assistance, and step-up to help Completion of Grade 12 It’s great if you have Additional courses related to the workAn understanding that digital literacy is a component of library services and are comfortable handling technology devices such as tablets, netbooks, and eReaders The hourly pay rate for this unionized position starts at $27.30 (2024 rates), based on a 35-hour workweek, plus a generous benefits package. This work requires flexible availability, including evenings and weekend shifts. North Vancouver District Public Library is an equal opportunity employer, committed to creating a diverse, inclusive, barrier-free work environment. If you have a passion for connecting community, sharing knowledge, and inspiring stories, and you are interested in joining our dynamic team, then we’d like to hear from you! Qualified applicants are invited to apply online only with your cover letter and resume at https://careers.dnv.org by July 9, 2024 to be considered for this competition. We thank you for your interest in employment with the North Vancouver District Public Library and advise that only those shortlisted for an interview will be contacted. Our libraries are located on the traditional territories of the səl̓ílwətaʔɬ/Selilwitulh (Tsleil-Waututh), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam) First Nations. We are grateful for the opportunity to connect community, share knowledge and inspire stories on unceded Coast Salish Territory. Compensation The hourly pay rate for this unionized position starts at $27.30 (2024 rates), based on a 35-hour workweek, plus a generous benefits package. Closes: 9 July, 2024 North Vancouver District Public Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
