ive relationships with staff, trustees and the public.Must have valid driver’s license and own transportation. Candidates will be required to provide a clean criminal records check should they be selected. Lac La Biche Country Libraries are committed to equity and diversity in the workplace and encourage applications from all qualified applicants.We are fully focused on equality and believe in diversity of race, gender, sexual orientation, religion, ethnicity, national origin and all the other characteristics that make us different. If interested, please send your resume and cover letter to llbclhrchair@gmail.com. This competition will remain open until the position is filled. We thank all applicants for their interest in our organization, however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted.https://www.llbcl.ca/About-Us2/Career Compensation $78,251.16 Closes: 17 July, 2024 Lac La Biche County Libraries Lac La Biche , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
